<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870424-0190 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:Mead to Split Stock,Boost Dividend 10%</HL><DD> 04/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MEADIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><DATELINE> DAYTON, Ohio  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mead Corp. directors approved a 2-for-1 stock split and a 10% increase in the quarterly dividend to 33 cents from 30 cents on a pre-split basis.    The paper products and information-retrieval concern said it will distribute one common share for each common share outstanding on June 1 to stock of record May 4. The higher dividend also will be paid June 1 to stock of record May 4.    At the annual meeting, stockholders approved a doubling of the number of authorized shares to 300 million.    Company officials said they intend to double to 800,000 tons Mead's capacity to produce coated natural kraft paperboard. Mead's sales of such paperboard have increased sharply in the U.S. and Japan. </TEXT></DOC>